text: Bjørne Jorgensen (December 16, 1893 - June 22, 1934) was an American gymnast. He competed in the men's artistic individual all-around event at the 1920 Summer Olympics. ==References== Category:1893 births Category:1934 deaths Category:American male artistic gymnasts Category:Olympic gymnasts of the United States Category:Gymnasts at the 1920 Summer Olympics Category:People from Asker
